The paper discusses a method for enabling full-duplex in many-antenna systems using digital beamforming. This involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.AR). However, given the focus on wireless communication and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories.
